{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "You are a Go engineer working on a Kubernetes operator.\nThe repository is located at /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment.\nChange your working directory to that repository before beginning.\n\nTask:\nAdd a new Prometheus counter metric named mto_ppo_ctrl_image_cache_hits_total with a\nlabel image_ref to internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/. Register it following\nthe pattern of existing metrics in that package.\n\nThen instrument it in the image cache layer (pkg/image/cache.go or pkg/image/facade.go)\nso it increments each time an architecture result is returned from cache rather than\nfetched from the registry.\n\n\nProduce a complete implementation. Include:\n- All files that must be modified with the exact changes\n- Any make targets or commands to run and in what order\n- The complete code for any new files or functions"}, "timestamp": "2026-07-20T18:06:25.854Z"}
